	doi = {10.1109/ISCI65687.2025.11167451},
	abstract = {This paper presents an automated system using Machine Learning (ML) techniques to improve cricket team selection. Traditional methods, relying on expert opinions and manual analysis, are often time-consuming and subject to biases. The proposed system uses ML algorithms to analyze key performance indicators like batting averages, bowling averages, strike rates, and economy rates, creating a predictive model for optimal player selection. The model also integrates factors such as player endurance, injury history, and recovery times, providing a holistic view of each player’s contribution. This data-driven approach reduces human errors and biases, offering more objective insights. The system is adaptable to different cricket formats—Test, One-Day International (ODI), and Twenty20 (T20)—with tailored strategies for each format’s unique demands. By selecting players not only on current form but also on physical preparedness, the model ensures a well-rounded team. This approach has the potential to transform team selection processes and influence broader cricket strategies, including training and in-game tactics.},
